main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Fukuoka, Japan on 5 August 1953.
interesting points: The object was a singular white, luminous, disc-shaped object observed at an altitude of approximately 10,000 feet., The object exhibited erratic and random course changes while moving at high speed., The sighting lasted around 30 seconds with no unusual sounds or trails observed., The object did not conform to the characteristics of any known aircraft or balloon., The report concluded the sighting was UNIDENTIFIED and lacked physical evidence.
witness description: The observer was not specified in detail but was likely a trained personnel based on the context of the report.
